@adidasy3 quietly debuted one of Spring/Summer 2027's biggest collaborations, teaming up with @numberninebytakahiromiyashita newly revived Number (N)ine. While the runway's high-energy choreography and football cameos stole much of the spotlight, the Japanese design meeting unfolded through an all-black collection blending Y-3's technical sportswear with Number (N)ine's signature grunge aesthetic.⁠
⁠
The standout was the footwear. At first glance, the shoes resemble sleek zip-up cross-country ski boots, but unzip the outer shell to reveal a classic leather hiking boot underneath. It's an inventive two-in-one design that feels genuinely fresh, proving what can happen when two of Japan's most influential designers share the same stage.⁠

