Kareena Kapoor Khan has been named the new face of MINI India, bringing together one of Bollywood’s most enduring style icons and one of the world’s most distinctive premium automotive brands.
The partnership reflects MINI’s focus on individuality, design, and modern luxury, with Kareena fronting the brand’s latest campaigns in India. As global luxury brands continue to deepen their presence in the country, collaborations like these highlight India’s growing influence in the premium lifestyle and automotive space.
@Mini #Luxurious

Jordyn Woods's orange bag has been credited with bringing the Knicks its first NBA Championship final win in 53 years. It has been blessed by New York City’s mayor, Zohran Mamdani. It even enjoyed the VIP treatment at a celebratory parade. It is now going to be exhibited at the Guggenheim Museum.
@jordynwoods, who is engaged to the Knicks center @karltowns, wore the leather clutch to all but one of the games in the lead up to the finals. On the days she brought the bag, which is from her own label, Woods by Jordyn, the Knicks won. (The day the team broke its winning streak was, coincidentally, the day that Madison Square Garden implemented a strict no-bag policy and heightened security for President Trump’s attendance.)
“This bag came to represent a cultural moment,” Mariët Westermann, the director of the Guggenheim, said. Tap the link in our bio to read more about the purse’s urban legend. Photos by The Hapa Blonde/GC Images, via Getty Images, Jordyn Woods

@celine closed Paris Men’s—and yes, it was hot. Literally and otherwise. For SS27, artistic director Michael Rider delivered his first standalone menswear runway for the house, stepping out of the co-ed format and into something more defined.
And as always, the styling was exciting, the tailoring sexy, and the details to-die-for. Drop your thoughts.
#Celine #ParisFashionWeek #Menswear #MichaelRider

“After 20 years together, getting married did not feel like a new beginning,” says Prayag Menon (@prayag.menon). “It felt like giving a name to a life that had already been lived,” Porus Vimadalal (@porus.vimadalal) chimes in.
When the occasion arrived, the pair chose one of love’s most enduring rituals to mark it: a pair of bespoke wedding bands set with natural diamonds. For generations, rings have signified devotion, continuity, and the promise of a shared future. What has changed is who gets to participate in that tradition. This Pride Month, their story offers a reminder that while social conventions continue to evolve, the desire to commemorate commitment with something lasting remains profoundly human.
@adarshhsoni in conversation with the couple at the link in bio.

