@saythename_17 may have just turned 11, but @joshu_acoustic is just getting started. This curious shift comes amidst a defining season for the K-pop group who is currently navigating their enlistment period, with members presently serving, or scheduled for conscription this year. 

This has led to a series of solo endeavours on the part of @voguesingapore's cover star for the 'Embody' issue, whose latest explorations include forays into the acting world, producing music and deeper ventures into the fashion world. "I think it helps that I am, by nature, a very open person, whether that is to new experiences or feelings," he quips with ease. 

In the link in bio, the inquisitive K-pop artist—who is one of two cover stars for our 'Embody issue—delves into the various creative roles he has been switching between, and reveals to us why this might be his most embodied season yet. Snag an issue of the June 'Embody' issue, out on newsstands now.

